ZH:我聘请了一名向导来带领我们前往山顶。
EN:I hired a guide to lead us to the top of the mountain.

ZH:向导带着我们穿过密林找到了古代遗迹。
EN:The guide led us through the dense jungle to find the ancient ruins.

ZH:这座城市的向导非常熟悉历史和地理。
EN:The guide in this city is very familiar with the history and geography.

ZH:向导告诉我们要小心蛇和其他野生动物。
EN:The guide warned us to be careful of snakes and other wildlife.

ZH:向导展示了一张古老地图，指引我们前往目的地。
EN:The guide displayed an ancient map to guide us to our destination.

ZH:他们雇了一名向导来带领他们跨越沼泽地。
EN:They hired a guide to lead them through the marshland.

ZH:向导解释道，这片森林里的植被非常丰富。
EN:The guide explained that the vegetation in this forest is very rich.

ZH:我们需要一名向导来帮助我们穿越这片荒凉的沙漠。
EN:We need a guide to help us cross this barren desert.

ZH:向导指挥着我们的船只穿过湖面上的岩石。
EN:The guide directed our boat through the rocks on the surface of the lake.

ZH:向导告诉我们要注意珊瑚礁，以免受伤。
EN:The guide told us to watch out for coral reefs to avoid getting hurt.

ZH:我戴着帽子，跟着向导走进瀑布的阴影。
EN:I wore a hat and followed the guide into the shadow of the waterfall.

ZH:向导提醒我们在登山时要保持警惕。
EN:The guide reminded us to stay vigilant while hiking.

ZH:只有经验丰富的向导才能带领我们登上这座险峻的山峰。
EN:Only an experienced guide can lead us to the summit of this steep mountain peak.

ZH:向导向我们介绍了这座城市的传统文化。
EN:The guide introduced us to the traditional culture of this city.

ZH:由于向导的照料，我们安然抵达了目的地。
EN:Thanks to the guide's care, we arrived safely at our destination.

ZH:向导帮助我们找到了基地，搭建了帐篷。
EN:The guide helped us find a campsite and set up tents.

ZH:向导告诉我们要遵守当地的风俗习惯。
EN:The guide told us to respect local customs.

ZH:这名向导在山中找到了一种可以治疗疾病的植物。
EN:The guide found a plant in the mountains that can cure diseases.

ZH:向导引导我们躲过了暴风雨。
EN:The guide led us to safety through the storm.

ZH:向导向我们展示了寻找食物的技巧。
EN:The guide showed us the skills of finding food.
